 :tx/rationale "Create task: DAEMON-3: W_α agent working set — in-memory telemetry without shared-store pollution (INV-STORE-013, INV-STORE-014, FD-012). BACKGROUND: FD-012 requires every command to record provenance. Currently RFL-2 predictions and AR-2 traces go to the shared store (txns/), invalidating caches. The spec (INV-STORE-013) defines W_α as a private working set invisible to other agents and excluded from merge. APPROACH: (1) Define WorkingSet struct in braid-kernel/src/store.rs: { local_datoms: BTreeSet<Datom>, agent: AgentId, created_at: u64 }. (2) WorkingSet::record(datom) — append to local_datoms. (3) WorkingSet::query_view(store) — returns iterator over store.datoms() ∪ local_datoms (W_α override). (4) WorkingSet::flush_to_file(path) — serialize to .braid/.cache/working_set.bin for crash recovery. (5) WorkingSet::load_from_file(path) — restore on daemon restart. (6) In daemon: RFL-2 predictions go to W_α instead of txns/. AR-2 traces go to W_α. Session auto-detect metadata goes to W_α. (7) W_α is NOT included in layout.write_tx() — it stays local. (8) On braid harvest --commit: optionally promote selected W_α datoms to shared store. ACCEPTANCE: (A) W_α datoms invisible via store.datoms(). (B) W_α datoms visible via working_set.query_view(store). (C) W_α not written to txns/. (D) Flush/load round-trip preserves all datoms. (E) RFL-2 in W_α does not invalidate store.bin cache. (F) Property: W_α ∩ visible(other_agent) = ∅. DEPENDS-ON: DAEMON-1 (t-0a1b5c4e). FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/store.rs, crates/braid/src/daemon.rs"
